# AutoDL Instance - AI Coding Rules

## High-Level Overview

### Architecture
This is a **plugin-based orchestration system** for automating AutoDL cloud GPU instance setup. It manages:
- ComfyUI installation and configuration
- Model downloading and management
- Network proxy configuration (mihomo/turbo)
- Git-based userdata synchronization

```
src/
├── main.py                 # Entry point, lifecycle orchestrator
├── core/                   # Core abstractions
│   ├── interface.py        # AppContext, BaseAddon, hookimpl
│   ├── artifacts.py        # Cross-plugin shared state (DTO)
│   ├── schema.py           # StateKey, EnvKey enums
│   ├── ports.py            # ICommandRunner, IStateManager
│   └── adapters.py         # Concrete implementations
├── addons/                 # Plugin modules
│   ├── system/             # UV, SSH, cache migration
│   ├── git_config/         # Git/SSH configuration
│   ├── torch_engine/       # PyTorch CUDA setup
│   ├── comfy_core/         # ComfyUI installation
│   ├── userdata/           # Userdata symlinks & git sync
│   ├── nodes/              # Custom nodes management
│   └── models/             # Model directory & lock management
└── lib/                    # Reusable libraries
    ├── download/           # Strategy-based download manager
    ├── network/            # Proxy & mirror management
    └── utils.py            # YAML, SHA256, format helpers
```

### Application Entry Points
- **Main Orchestrator**: `python -m src.main {setup|start|sync}`
  - `setup`: Initialize environment (runs once per instance)
  - `start`: Launch ComfyUI service
  - `sync`: Sync state to git, generate model-lock.yaml

- **Standalone CLI**: `python -m src.addons.models.downloader download <url> --type <type>`

### Plugin Execution Order (Hardcoded)
```python
# src/main.py:create_pipeline()
# sync 动作逆序执行
[SystemAddon, GitAddon, TorchAddon, ComfyAddon, UserdataAddon, NodesAddon, ModelAddon]
```

