## Critical Rules Summary

### MUST DO
- [ ] All functions have type hints
- [ ] All files start with docstring
- [ ] Plugin classes set `module_dir` = directory name
- [ ] Use `@hookimpl` decorator for lifecycle methods
- [ ] Check idempotency with `ctx.state.is_completed()`
- [ ] Log with `logger.info("  -> ...")` pattern
- [ ] Handle symlink OSError for Windows compatibility

### NEVER DO
- [ ] Hardcode paths (use `ctx.base_dir`, `ctx.comfy_dir`)
- [ ] Commit `secrets.yaml` (only `.example`)
- [ ] Skip type hints on public functions
- [ ] Use magic strings for state keys (use `StateKey` enum)
- [ ] Assume plugin order (read from `ctx.artifacts`)

### Performance Notes
- YAML loading: Use `load_yaml()` (handles missing files)
- SHA256: Incremental hash with chunked reads (8KB)
- Model scan: Filter 0-byte files and placeholders early
- Network: Cached decision avoids re-initializing proxy

